Parliament, Friday, 12 March 2021 – The Chairperson of the Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, Ms Faith Muthambi, has learnt with sadness of the passing of His Majesty King Goodwill Zwelithini ka Bhekuzulu, King of the Zulu Nation.
	
	Ms Muthambi said: “His Majesty King Zwelithini was a beacon of hope and the pillar of the Zulu nation since he assumed the throne of kingship. Throughout his kingship tenure, at times that were marked by bitter political struggles for the transformation of South African society, King Zwelithini remained at the side of his people as a symbol of strength and peace.
	
	“The committee extends its deepest condolences to the Zwelithini family and relatives, the Zulu nation and the entire South African nation. May his soul rest in eternal peace,” said Ms Muthambi.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON COOPERATIVE GOVERNANCE AND TRADITIONAL AFFAIRS, MS FAITH MUTHAMBI.
	
